<h2><a name="set" id="set">set</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;bitset&gt;</span>
    bitset<span class="sy0">&lt;</span>N<span class="sy0">&gt;&amp;</span> set<span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
    bitset<span class="sy0">&lt;</span>N<span class="sy0">&gt;&amp;</span> set<span class="br0">&#40;</span> size_t pos<span class="sy0">,</span> bool val<span class="sy0">=</span><span class="kw2">true</span> <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;</pre>
<p>
The set() function sets all of the bits in the bitset, and returns the bitset.
If pos is specified, then only the bit at position pos is set.
If val is specified, then the bit is set or reset depending on the value of val.
</p>

